<br>
I announce beggars in /ooc.  You can differentiate that way between n00b beggars who don't know any better and the scumballs who are just too lazy to play the game.  True noobs will be ashamed and stop.  The idiots will start whining and yelling back saying something moronic like, &quot;I have a lvl 60 on another server who culd kick ur a**!&quot;  At which I reply, &quot;If you truly had a lvl 60, you'd know how to make money other than begging.&quot;  Being sickly sweet and condescending just infuriates them which makes for nice /report material. ;-)  Never hurts to give Verant a heads-up on the future scammers and KSers.  <br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong - I love giving stuff away to true newbies.  I remember the thrill of wielding my fine steel weapon or how cool I thought I was in a full suit of banded. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But the instant they ask me for anything other than a buff, they lose any chance of getting goodies, period.<br>
<br>
The one thing that really ticks me off is people who say that everyone has begged at some point.  That just isn't true.  I have NEVER asked for stuff from strangers.  The most I've begged for is a mercy sow for a heckuva long corpse recovery. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I didn't say something lame like &quot;sow plz&quot; either.  hehe  But that's another thread or two. ;-)  <br>
<br>
Appletartt Pyepann<br>
